When you decide to upload your commits.

Problems is here.
Very long time ago, GitHub Offical use email-address and password
to verify whether the access user is the true user who owns the repo.

But it is very fragile, because the password is easy to guess.
Or it is dangerous, because the password can be leaked to others.
Like, if you copy paste the password, or just do something wrong.

So use SSH protocol to transfer files is a relative safe operation.

SSH protocol with SSH pub-key verification is becoming a very popluar way 
to transfer files through the network.

